{
  "description": "This diagram illustrates an architecture for **Agent2Agent Interoperability**, centered around **SAP BTP**.\n\nSAP BTP hosts internal agents (built with Joule Agent Builder) and provides an **Agent Catalog** (using ORD for registration and A2A for routing) and an **Agent Connector**. This system enables internal SAP applications and agents to discover and interact with each other, and also to connect with and leverage external AI agents hosted on major cloud platforms like **Google Cloud (Vertex AI), Microsoft Azure (AI Foundry), and AWS (Bedrock Agents)**, each having their own agent connectors and catalogs.",
